FBIS3-47526 "dreas009_l_94004" FBIS-EAS-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 Philippines MILF Ready To Sign Separate Cease-Fires Accord BK1301071794 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 0500 GMT 13 Jan 94 BK1301071794 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network Language: Tagalog Article Type:BFN [Text] The Moro Islamic Liberation Front [MILF] is ready to sign an agreement with the Philippine Government for the implementation of separate cease fires. Government panel member Eduardo Ermita made this announcement after receiving hints from the MILF headed by Hashem Salamat. Earlier, government panel Chairman Manuel Yan disclosed that the government will hold separate peace talks with the MILF after the negotiation with the MNLF [Moro National Liberation Front] headed by Nur Misuari. [Begin recording, in English, in progress] [Ermita] ... and MNLF. [Unidentified reporter] But what about the cease-fire processes? [Ermita] When we came from Jakarta, we got word that they [MILF] are considering signing a separate cease-fire agreement, but we have never been able to confirm that. [Reporter] Will the cease-fire agreement depend on what took place during the talks with MNLF? [Ermita] No, it is independent of the MNLF. We are still awaiting, lahat eh.... [changes thought], we have not gotten any final word from the MILF whether indeed they will sign a separate cease-fire agreement with the Philippine Government. [end recording]
